Poison resilience
+1 saves vs Poison effects

Venom (Su)
Your saliva contains an anesthetizing venom that acts as an injury poison.
You are immune to the effects of this venom, but creatures exposed to your saliva
  must succeed on a DC11+ConMod Fort save or be paralyzed for 1d6 rounds.
Note: This is not a contact poison - you can not simply spit on someone's arm to affect them.
  You must introduce your saliva to the bloodstream or a mucous membrane.

FireResist 5

